News & Announcements

 
The men of St. Paul's Baptist Church would like to thank everyone for making our Men's Day Service a blessed day in the Lord.  Thanks to everyone who played a part in the service and to everyone who came out to support us! 
St. Paul's Baptist Church, Conshohocken
 
Our Easter Play will be held on April 24 after the morning service!  This year's play is entitled "Dawn of the Dead Living".  If you would like to be a part of the play, please see Deaconess Joyce Mangum.  Check the calendar for rehearsal dates and times!
 
 
St. Paul's would like to extend a special thanks to Myrna Graham for her many years of service to our beloved church. Her presence in the pulpit will surely be missed by all. It is good to know that she is doing better and continues to get stronger. Our prayers and thoughts are with her.
 
Thank you again Pastor Graham and best wishes.
 
St. Paul's Baptist Church, Conshohocken

Points of Power


The LORD is my shepherd; I shall not want. He maketh me to lie down in green pastures: he leadeth me beside the still waters. He restoreth my soul: he leadeth me in the paths of righteousness for his name's sake. Yea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil: for thou art with me; thy rod and thy staff they comfort me. Thou preparest a table before me in the presence of mine enemies: thou anointest my head with oil; my cup runneth over. Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me all the days of my life: and I will dwell in the house of the LORD for ever.


Psalm 23

Commit to the LORD whatever you do, and your plans will succeed.

Proverbs 16:3
 

Don't you know that you yourselves are God's temple and that God's Spirit lives in you?


I Corinthians 3:16
